reviewText: Love this movie. The DVD was brand new and not too bad of a quality for how old the movie is.

I really enjoyed this movie. I thought it was pretty good. It's probably not for everybody,but Stephen Chow was funny. Sort of like a J. Chan movie. Transported back in time because he used powerful kung-fu he finds himself in early 1900's Shanghai. He gets job with good guy gambler and falls in love. I won't say any more because I don't want to ruin it,however it was a pretty good movie. Also,Gong Li as twins adds something special.
